e soup as a starter while turkey rests. Slice turkey and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dry Brine","content":["½ oz fresh rosemary, leaves only","2 oz salt","2 oz dried apple","3 heaping tbsp black peppercorns","1 lemon, thin peel only, no pith","1 oz coriander seeds","1 oz juniper berries","2 dried bay leaves"]},{"title":"Spice Rub","content":["2 limes, thin peel only, no pith","2 lemons, thin peel only, no pith","2 tsp salt","1 tsp freshly ground black pepper","2 tsp ground turmeric","1 pinch saffron","2 garlic cloves","2 dried chilies","1 heaping tsp sweet paprika","1 heaping tsp sugar"]},{"title":"Turkey Breast and Potato Soup","content":["35 oz turkey breast half, skin on, bone in","3 oz red onions, quartered","2 oz unsalted butter","32 oz chicken stock","30 oz Yukon gold potatoes, peeled and quartered","freshly ground black pepper, to taste","salt, to taste","fresh rosemary, to garnish"]}],"id":"r164642","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ghqwakVMrEY\/XZMt34t5WWI\/AAAAAAAAZ-c\/Yf8mmRgo7gs8ZZMP0nlROLKuhEXBxfIswCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2il5mF8refTDWqON.png","title":"Turkey Breast with Creamy Potato Soup","publishedAt":"2017-10-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"34 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"1556 kJ \/ 372 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towels, large freezer bag, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If using two turkey breasts place one in the Varoma tray and one in the Varoma dish, half way through the cooking swap them around. You may need to increase the cooking time.","After steaming turkey breast, keep spices left in Varoma dish to make a gravy. Place leftover spices, 6 oz water, 1 tsp vegetable stock paste and 1 tbsp corn starch into mixing bowl and mix <strong>7 min\/195°F\/speed 4<\/strong>.","For added flavor: increase brine spice by 1 oz each fresh rosemary, ground coriander and juniper berries.","Turkey may also be served or garnished with homemade Spiced Cranberry Orange Sauce."],"basicInfo":["easy","